data.name: label68.Text
data.value: Check the table below if the plugin was able to parse all music videos located in your Import Paths defined above. Music Videos not parsed correctly will be highlighted. If renaming your files does not help, you can modify the plugins parser behaviour from the left hand side.

data.name: label69.Text
data.value:
String Replacements can be used to remove common string patterns that may confuse the plugins parsing engine. It can also be helpful in replacing strange names that may not get automatically matched e.g: replace 'fnas' with 'Formally known as Prince'
Be sure to enable 'run before matching' for this to work before it reaches the parsing engine.

data.name: label70.Text
data.value:
Parsing Expressions are used by the plugins parsing engine to retrieve a Artist, Album and Track from a Folder Structure / Filename in your Import Paths. This information is required to successfully match up with the online database.
If an expression can not evaluate these items, the next expression in the list is used.
